  <description>
    <p>Music Assistant is a free, opensource Media library manager that connects to your streaming services and a wide range of connected speakers. 
    The server is the beating heart, the core of Music Assistant and must run on an always-on device like a Raspberry Pi, a NAS or an Intel NUC or alike. </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Acces the Music Assistant UI.</li>
      <li>Play music to your PC from Music Assistant.</li>
      <li>Discord Rich Presence (can be disabled)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Note: To connect to your Music Assistant server you must have the webserver exposed. And to allow playback to the companion app you must also add the Slimproto provider in the Music Assistant settings. Check the GitHub for instructions.</p>
  </description>

